properties.areaDesc: Chesapeake Bay from Sandy Point to North Beach MD; Chesapeake Bay from Drum Point MD to Smith Point VA; Chesapeake Bay from North Beach to Drum Point MD; Tidal Potomac from Cobb Island MD to Smith Point VA; Tangier Sound and the inland waters surrounding Bloodsworth Island
properties.headline: Marine Weather Statement issued January 16 at 12:54AM EST by NWS Baltimore MD/Washington DC
properties.description:
A few southerly wind gusts to around 20 knots are possible
overnight for the Maryland portion of the Chesapeake Bay, mainly
between Sandy Point Maryland and Smith Point Virginia, as well as
the tidal Potomac River below Cobb Island Maryland.

Mariners, especially those in smaller vessels, should exercise
extra caution if navigating the waters during this time.

NWSheadline: OCCASIONAL WIND GUSTS TO AROUND 20 KNOTS
